'''Kiryat Shlomo''' ({{lang-he|×§×¨×××ª ×©×××}}, lit. ''Place of Shlomo'') is a therapeutic community in [[Israel]]. It falls within the jurisdiction of [[Hof HaSharon Regional Council]] and had a population of {{Israel populations|Qiryat Shelomo}} in {{Israel populations|Year}}.{{Israel populations|reference}}

==History==
The community was established in 1945.<ref name=Israelpopulations/>

