{{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Lun Htar Htar | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = {{my|áá½ááºá¸áá¬á¸áá¬á¸}} | native_name_lang = my | pseudonym = | birth_name = Hta Hta Lin | birth_date = {{b-da|8 June 1971}} | birth_place = [[Rangoon]], [[Burma]] | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = | language = [[Burmese language|Burmese]] | nationality = | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = [[MBBS]] | alma_mater = [[University of Medicine 1, Yangon]] | period = | genre = Fiction | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = <!-- or: | notablework = --> | spouse = Unt Tun Maung | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
'''Lun Hta Hta''' ({{lang-my|áá½ááºá¸áá¬á¸áá¬á¸}}; also spelled '''Lun Htar Htar''') is a prolific Burmese writer, having written over 300 novels throughout her career.<ref name="ytp">{{cite news|url=http://www.yatanarpon.com.mm/entertainment/book/author_bio/%E1%80%9C%E1%80%BC%E1%80%94%E1%80%B9%E1%80%B8%E1%80%91%E1%80%AC%E1%80%B8%E1%80%91%E1%80%AC%E1%80%B8|title=áá½ááºá¸áá¬á¸áá¬á¸|date=25 March 2011|work=Yatanarpon|language=Burmese|accessdate=17 July 2015}}</ref><ref name="irr">{{cite news|url=http://www.irrawaddy.org/burma/uk-based-burmese-doctor-jailed-for-fondling-female-patient-reports.html|title=UK-Based Burmese Doctor Jailed for Fondling Female Patient: Reports|date=20 April 2015|work=The Irrawaddy|accessdate=17 July 2015}}</ref>
Lun Hta Hta was born on 8 June 1971 in [[Rangoon]], [[Burma]] to parents Soe Thway and Mya Yi.<ref name="ytp"/> Her birth name is '''Hta Hta Lin''' ({{my|áá¬á¸áá¬á¸áááºá¸}}).<ref name="ytp"/> She matriculated from [[Basic Education High School No. 2 Dagon]] in 1987, earning distinctions in 4 subjects on the national matriculation exam.<ref name="ytp"/> She pursued further studies at [[University of Medicine 1, Yangon]], graduating with an [[MBBS]] degree in 1998.<ref name="ytp"/> She is married to a [[British people|British]] physician, Unt Tun Maung, and presently resides in [[England]].<ref name="el">{{cite news|url=http://www.news-eleven.com/%E1%80%B1%E1%80%86%E1%80%AC%E1%80%84%E1%80%B9%E1%80%B8%E1%80%95%E1%80%AB%E1%80%B8%E1%80%99%E1%80%BA%E1%80%AC%E1%80%B8/%E1%80%A1%E1%80%82%E1%81%A4%E1%80%9C%E1%80%94%E1%80%B9%E1%80%B1%E1%80%9B%E1%80%AC%E1%80%80%E1%80%B9-%E1%80%BB%E1%80%99%E1%80%94%E1%80%B9%E1%80%99%E1%80%AC%E1%80%86%E1%80%9B%E1%80%AC%E1%81%80%E1%80%94%E1%80%B9%E1%80%90%E1%80%85%E1%80%B9%E1%80%B1%E1%80%9A%E1%80%AC%E1%80%80%E1%80%B9%E1%81%8F-%E1%80%A1%E1%80%99%E1%82%88%E1%80%80%E1%80%AD%E1%80%85%E1%81%A5%E1%82%8F%E1%80%BD%E1%80%84%E1%80%B7%E1%80%B9%E1%80%95%E1%80%90%E1%80%B9%E1%80%9E%E1%80%80%E1%80%B9%E1%81%8D|title=á¡ááºá¹ááááºáá±á¬ááº áá¼ááºáá¬ááá¬áááºáá áºáá±á¬ááºá á¡áá¾á¯áá­á á¹á áá¾áá·áºáááºáááºá . . .|last=áááºá¸áá½ááº|work=Eleven News|accessdate=17 July 2015|language=Burmese}}</ref><ref name="ml">{{cite news|url=http://www.yatanarpon.com.mm/news/news-3634|title=áááºá¹ááá¬ áááºáááºá¸ (á)áá¾á áºáá¼áá·áº á¡áááºá¸á¡áá¾ááºáá½á²áá­á¯ áá­áá¬á¸á á¯áá²á· áá»ááºá¸ááá­á¯á· áá¼ááºáá¬áá­á¯ááºáá¶ áá¼ááºáá¬áá²á· áá½ááºá¸áá¬á¸áá¬á¸ áá­áá¬á¸á á¯|date=27 January 2011|work=Yatanarpon|accessdate=17 July 2015|language=Burmese}}</ref>
