{{Italic title}} {{Infobox book | image = Proof of Heaven A Neurosurgeon's Journey into the Afterlife.jpg | author = [[Eben Alexander (author)|Eben Alexander]] | name = Proof of Heaven: A Neurosurgeon's Journey into the Afterlife | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[Spirituality]] | publisher = [[Simon & Schuster]] | release_date = October 23, 2012 | media_type = Print ([[hardcover]] and [[paperback]]) | pages = 196 | isbn = 978-1451695199 | followed_by = ''The Map of Heaven'' }}
'''''Proof of Heaven: A Neurosurgeon's Journey into the Afterlife''''' is a 2012 auto-biographical book written by the American [[neurosurgeon]] [[Eben Alexander (author)|Eben Alexander III]]. It relates and discusses his memories of experiences during a [[coma]]. __NOTOC__ ==Summary== In the fall of 2008, Alexander, a doctor at Lynchburg General Hospital in Virginia, contracted a very rare [[bacterial meningitis]] and spent seven days in a coma. During this state, Alexander experienced something that gave him reason to believe in consciousness after death. In this book Alexander relates the details of his experience from the point of view of a neurosurgeon and discusses how this has affected his views on life, philosophy and medicine.
==Reception== ''Proof of Heaven'' reached the top 10 list in ''[[USA Today]]''{{'}}s 150 top selling titles.<ref>[http://books.usatoday.com/list/index ''Best-Selling Books: What America's Reading''], ''[[USA Today]]''. Retrieved November 18, 2012</ref> It has also reached number 1 on ''New York Times''{{'}} best selling paperback nonfiction books, <ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/overview.html ''Best Sellers''], ''[[New York Times]]''. Retrieved November 18, 2012</ref> number 3 on ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' best sellers, <ref>[http://projects.latimes.com/bestsellers/ ''This week's bestsellers''], ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''. Retrieved November 18, 2012</ref> and is included on [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] Best Sellers of 2012. ''Proof of Heaven'' was featured in Newsweek<ref>[http://newsweek.tumblr.com/post/33080596787/when-leading-neurosurgeon-dr-eben-alexander-found ''Heaven is Real:A Doctor's Experience of the Afterlife''] (cover image), [[Newsweek]], October 15, 2012. Retrieved on November 18, 2012</ref> and Dr. Alexander's story was presented on [[ABC news]] [[Nightline]].<ref>Marsh, Mary and Moran, Terry, [http://abcnews.go.com/Health/neuroscientist-sees-proof-heaven-week-long-coma/story?id=17555207 ''Neuroscientist Sees "Proof of Heaven" in Week-Long Coma''], [[ABC News]], October 24, 2012. Retrieved on November 18, 2012</ref> Some scepticism and criticism has been received, as well as praise.<ref>Wendy-Marie Teichert, [http://catholicbusinessjournal.biz/content/book-review-proof-heaven-neurosurgeon%E2%80%99s-journey-afterlife ''BOOK REVIEW: *Proof of Heaven: A Neurosurgeon's Journey into the Afterlife*''], Catholic Business Journal</ref><ref>Michael Shermer, [http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=why-near-death-experience-isnt-proof-heaven ''Why a Near-Death Experience Isnât Proof of Heaven''], [[Scientific American]], 19 March 2013</ref><ref>Donald S. Whitney, [http://biblicalspirituality.org/resources/book-reviews/book-reviewsproof-of-heaven-by-eben-alexander-iii/ ''Proof of Heaven by Eben Alexander III (review)''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140518033540/http://biblicalspirituality.org/resources/book-reviews/book-reviewsproof-of-heaven-by-eben-alexander-iii/ |date=2014-05-18 }}, The Center for Biblical Spirituality, 2013</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=''Proof of Heaven reviews''|url=http://www.christianbook.com/proof-heaven-neurosurgeons-journey-into-afterlife/alexander-eben/9781451695199/pd/695199?item_code=WW&netp_id=1044206&event=ESRCG&view=details|publisher=Christianbook.com}}</ref>
